r width\nfrom the likelihood ($\\times 1.2$ larger than the uncertainty when the true\ncovariance is used). Stronger priors on the covariance matrix reduce the\nmisestimation of parameter uncertainties to $<1\\%$. As expected, empirical\nestimates perform better with higher $N_{\\mathrm{real}}$, ameliorating the\nadverse effects on parameter constraints.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 7 Oct 2021 04:47:52 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 12 Oct 2021 02:02:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-14"}
