lly contaminated data. With substantially improved source\nmodels, upgraded analysis algorithms and enhanced data quality metrics, we\ndetermine EoR power spectrum upper limits based on analysis of the best\n$\\sim$14-hours data observed during 2015 and 2014 at redshifts 6.5, 6.8 and\n7.1, with the lowest $2\\sigma$ upper limit at z=6.5 of $\\Delta^2 \\leq (73.78\n~\\mathrm{mK)^2}$ at $k=0.13~\\mathrm{h~ Mpc^{-1}}$, improving on previous EoR1\nmeasurement results.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 7 Oct 2021 05:31:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-10-20"}
